Police in Kisumu are looking for a 34-year-old man suspected of killing his mother in Ting’a village, Seme Sub-County.  Michael Odhiambo reportedly fled the scene moments after the attack, evading a mob.  Witnesses said the suspect attacked his mother after a family dispute, slashing her several times with a machete before fleeing.  Seline Adhiambo died on the spot. Residents who responded to her screams for help were unable to rescue her.   A police officer told The Standard he found the woman dead. “She was lying in a pool of blood with deep cuts on her head,” said the officer.  Traders risk life and limb and as gangs fight for control of markets  Nyonje beats four-time national champ Magana at Kisumu Open  Kisumu Lady Bucks eye first win against Strathmore University  All set for Kisumu Open Rapid Chess tournament Wilfred Ochieng, a witness, said the incident had shocked the village.   “We do not understand why he had to commit that heinous act. We hope the suspect will be brought to book,” Ochieng' said.  Yesterday, by the time of going to press, the suspect was still on the run. County Commander Richard Ng'eno said they were on his trails and would ensure he is brought to book.   “The motive of the killing has not been established,” said Mr Ngeno.     NEW RED-ZONE? Spike in counties with low numbers with Kisumu registering new infections of Covid-19  Azma ya Vihiga Queens: Wanatarajia kuicharaza Kisumu Starlets, mechi itachezwa kesho ugani Moi  Crowds Nightmare: Kisumu residents disregard Covid-19 protocols during Madaraka day celebrations By Harold Odhiambo | 1 hour ago By Edwin Nyarangi | 5 hours ago By Harold Odhiambo | 9 hours ago By Kevine Omollo  | 17 hours ago